<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=International_auxiliary_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.rickharrison.com/language/optimal.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rickharrison.com/language/optimal.html" rel="nofollow">Proposed Guidelines for the Design of an Optimal International Auxiliary Language</a> — An article written by Richard K. Harrison.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Athens/Forum/5037/sapir.html" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/Athens/Forum/5037/sapir.html" rel="nofollow">The Function of an International Auxiliary Language</a> — An article written by linguist <a href="/wiki/Edward_Sapir" title="Edward Sapir">Edward Sapir</a> discussing the need for prospects of an international language.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.rickharrison.com/language/farewell.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rickharrison.com/language/farewell.html" rel="nofollow">Farewell to auxiliary languages</a>, a criticism of the auxiliary language movement by Richard K. Harrison.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.geocities.com/auxilinguaproject/" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/auxilinguaproject/" rel="nofollow">The Auxilingua Project</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ial.wikia.com/wiki/Main_Page" class="external text" title="http://ial.wikia.com/wiki/Main_Page" rel="nofollow">IAL Wiki</a> — a wiki for the Auxlang Community.</li>
<li><a href="http://onetongue.com" class="external text" title="http://onetongue.com" rel="nofollow">OneTongue.com</a> — A project for promoting a world auxiliary language.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Qwertie256/misc/which-ial.html" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/Qwertie256/misc/which-ial.html" rel="nofollow">Which International Auxiliary Language (IAL) should you learn?</a></li>
</ul>
